9 A PERSON OPERATING A BICYCLE, PLAY VEHICLE, OR UNICYCLE AT AN
10 INTERSECTION WHO IS FACING A RED SIGNAL MAY ENTER THE INTERSECTION TO
11 CROSS THE HIGHWAY IN THE DIRECTION OF A PEDESTRIAN CONTROL “WALK”
12 SIGNAL.
13 (2) BEFORE ENTERING AN INTERSECTION AS DESCRIBED IN
14 PARAGRAPH (1) OF THIS SUBSECTION, A PERSON OPERATING A BICYCLE, PLAY
15 VEHICLE, OR UNICYCLE SHALL YIELD THE RIGHT–OF–WAY TO ANY VEHICLE OR
16 PEDESTRIAN LAWFULLY USING THE INTERSECTION.
17 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
18 October 1, 2025.

